getCapabilitiesProvider

public static oracle.wireless.device.capability.CapabilitiesProvider getCapabilitiesProvider(java.lang.String location)
                                                                                      throws DeviceRepException
This method will return a singleton instance of the CapabilityProvider
By default the XML files are assumed to be in the directory structure - oracle/wireless/device/capability/agent, in the classpath. If you need to pass a different directory structure for the capabilities.xml file in the classpath, this method can be used. Please note that the location to be passed should be relative to the classpath 
eg: your classpath is: D:\myclasses;D:\mylib\myfiles.jar
 if your capabilities.xml is 
 a) located in D:\myclasses\meta-inf\agent\capabilities.xml
 then the parameter location will be set to : /meta-inf/agent/capabilities.xml 
 b) located in  D:\mylib\myfiles.jar under directory /meta-inf/agent/capabilities.xml 
 then the parameter location will be set to: /meta-inf/agent/capabilities.xml

Parameters:
location - location of the capabilities.xml file
Returns:
an instance of the capabilitiesProvider
Throws:
DeviceRepException

getCapabilitiesProvider

public static oracle.wireless.device.capability.CapabilitiesProvider getCapabilitiesProvider(java.lang.String baseLoc,
                                                                                             java.lang.String protocol)
                                                                                      throws DeviceRepException
This method returns a singleton instance of CapabilityProvider

Parameters:
baseLoc - location of the XML files
protocol - this can take values DevRepConst.PROTOCOL_HTTP, DevRepConst.PROTOCOL_HTTPS, DevRepConst.PROTOCOL_FILE 
 Eg: If the files are located on the File System eg. at 
       "D:\devrep\oracle\wireless\device\capability"  then this method
       can be called as follows
    getCapabilitiesProvider( "D:\devrep", DevRepConst.PROTOCOL_FILE ); 
       
       If the files are located on a web server, eg. at
       "devrep.us.oracle.com/devrep/oracle/wireless/device/capability".
        Then this method is called as follows:
     getCapabilitiesProvider( "devrep.us.oracle.com/devrep/", DevRepConst.PROTOCOL_HTTP )
Returns:
An instance of the CapabilitiesProvider
Throws:
DeviceRepException

getCapabilities

public java.util.Map getCapabilities(java.util.Map searchMap)
                              throws DeviceRepException
Get capabilities based upon the search string. If there is no exact match then if the agent type is specified, a minimum set of capabilities will be returned. Else an empty list will be returned.

Parameters:
searchMap - Map for which the capabilities are to be evaluated For example: Map can be "agents=ie,platforms=windows". One should use the DevRepConst class defined attributes for constructing the Search String.
Returns:
map that has all the capabilities of the device that matches the Search String. For example: returns can be- [dom form] [accessKeys false] The Map key will be the match the element names for the capabilities, and the values are of type String.
Throws:
DeviceRepException

getCapabilities

public java.util.Map getCapabilities(java.lang.String devicename)
                              throws DeviceRepException
Get capabilities based upon the device name.

Parameters:
devicename - Name of the device. It can be a logical or real device. GetDevice() method can be used to obtain the device name.
Returns:
map that has all the capabilities for the device and return NULL if device is not found. For example: It can contain following attributes- [dom form] [accessKeys false] The Map key will be the match the element names for the capabilities, and the values are of type String.
Throws:
DeviceRepException
